[00:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Search is changing. The way people find brands, discover products, and make decisions is being rebuilt around AI. And the rules that governed how you show up and the SEO playbook that took 20 years to write are being rewritten'

[00:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'faster than most marketing organizations can read them. But here\'s the bit that doesn\'t get talked about enough. This isn\'t just a text problem. It isn\'t about rewriting website copy,'

[00:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'restructuring your content for AI crawlers. The shift is multimodal. Video, image, audio, the full breadth of how a brand expresses itself is now part'

[00:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of how AI understands and describes you. And the brands that grasp that earliest are already pulling ahead. Welcome back to the Pencil Perspective.'

[00:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I\'m Tim. Joined today by Toby, Pencil\'s CEO, who has stepped in for Will. Hi, Toby. &gt;&gt; Hi, Tim. &gt;&gt; And today our guest is Jack Smythe. Hi, Jack.'

[01:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Hi, how\'s it going, Tim? &gt;&gt; So, Jack is country lead for Australia at the BrandTech Group. And before that, he was a partner at BrandTech Media Group and spent time at Jellyfish, the'

[01:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'group\'s media and performance arm, which is where a lot of the thinking on Geo and share of model has been developed. What that career arc gives Jack is something genuinely rare in this conversation. He\'s someone who\'s watched'

[01:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'media innovation evolve from the inside at scale across markets for some of the world\'s biggest brands. And who is now sitting inside the organization that is building the tools to navigate the next'

[01:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'shift. Today, Jack\'s going to make the case that video is the most underestimated signal in geo. Jack, you\'ve been working in media innovation for a pretty long time. You\'ve seen'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'waves of change come through. Programmatic, social, data-driven. Where does geo sit in that history for you? Is this another wave or is this structurally different? &gt;&gt; It\'s a fantastic question, because I'

[02:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'think it\'s a another wave that actually loops back a lot of the lessons that many marketers have learned over the course of their careers.'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, let\'s take video as an example from your great introduction, Tim. We\'ve known for decades that video is the most effective way to capture a human\'s attention, and it\'s the most effective format to convey what makes your brand'

[02:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'unique. It just so happens that the more we learn about how AI models learn about the world and brands and products, that video has turned out to be the most effective format to capture their'

[02:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'attention. So, it is a seismic shift. I think every marketer has to realize that every single brief that they write has a new audience. The AI models that act on behalf of their human audiences.'

