VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Absolutely. I think, you know, you\'ve hit the nail on the head there that there is a fear and a risk that if we just stick to GEO as the linear evolution of SEO, we\'re not really capturing the full'

[08:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'picture. And to treat GEO as just the next stage of SEO where your web content is the primary input, that really ignores the fact that these models and these generative engines are'

[09:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'multimodal. So, they can read, they can look at an image and understand the composition, the color, the gradient, everything in the background of Tim\'s photo for example. They can listen to audio. They'

[09:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'hopefully recognize I have an Australian accent. That\'s why I sound better than all of you. &gt;&gt; All right. Right. Right. Right. Right. &gt;&gt; And then they can watch video. You can see your kind of, you know, uh your reply to that comment and'

[09:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'understand that you don\'t agree with that sentiment at all. &gt;&gt; Well, I\'m from Barbados, so I still rate. &gt;&gt; Well, I mean, okay, so the second best accent on this call. But, to that point, the last 15 seconds of this podcast would teach a model a'

[09:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lot about us. And there\'s a wealth of information that\'s encoded in those modalities of video, audio, image, and text. So, as a marketer, if you\'re really only focusing on text, which if you boil down'

[10:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'GEO to primarily being content on your website that can be referenced and indexed and cited, well, you can already see you\'re missing at least 75% of the picture.'

[10:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And then you can go back to what we spoke around history repeating itself, uh video is a much better way to express your brand. You know, a blog post saying the seven reasons that I love, uh for example, you know, Hellmann\'s'

[10:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mayonnaise, may be a great set of factual reasons about why it\'s healthy for you, it\'s versatile, and it makes delicious sandwiches. But, to watch someone bite in to a recipe made with Hellmann\'s and smile, that gives the model a much'

[10:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'better idea about that\'s a brand that people aspire to or want or feel enjoyment around. So, multimodality means we go from GEO to GEM.'

[10:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And GEM is generative engine marketing. It reflects the broader scope of all of the levers that a marketing team can pull to shape the perception of their brand'

[11:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and ensure that that model is ultimately going to be the ultimate influencer. It will have the best opinion of your brand, which will make them more likely to recommend your brand. It will reference your content as a great expression of what makes you'

[11:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'unique. And in that case, this isn\'t a job for an SEO team. It\'s a job for a CMO. Why would that model choose your brand? And how do you make sure every asset you publish across all those modalities represents the best your brand can be?'

