VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'won\'t have heard of share of model before. So, could you give me some of the basics of what is it and what does it measure? And why is it a better frame than the metrics that CMOs might already'

[12:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have on their dashboards? &gt;&gt; Absolutely. Share of model is a platform that we launched in 2023. So, well before the current hype wave that has seen close to 1.8 billion'

[12:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dollars invested in these tools. And we were the &gt;&gt; All right. &gt;&gt; We were the first platform to market. We were the first platform to embrace the potential of multimodality. So, if you think of GEM as the'

[13:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'capability, share of model is the metric. And we specifically call it share of model cuz we believe just as you track your share of voice, you should track your share of model. Model recommendations that reference'

[13:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your brand. And our work with leading publishers like Harvard Business Review, where we conducted a longitudinal study looking at four different categories in the biggest markets around the world, found'

[13:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that the brands with the highest share of model also grew their share of market faster than the average competitor. So, it\'s best to think of your share of model as a leading metric. The greater your share of model recommendations, the'

[13:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'greater your share of market. And it\'s a platform that we launched that help brands then start to unpack how models think about their brand and then critically which assets are driving and contributing to that perception.'

[13:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, it started from a very humble place. We used a handful of the world\'s most influential models and very simply we ask them questions every single day to articulate their reasoning and their rationale.'

[14:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Then we started to unpick the language of these large language models to look for patterns. And in that case, we\'re not like any of those other geo visibility platforms that record a couple of hundred prompts and hope that they\'re representative.'

[14:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We\'re really focused on the patterns in model responses that allow you to understand the underlying associations that are formed in their training set. So, it\'s a really foundational insight about how these models think about your'

[14:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'brand. Cuz that empowers marketers to create whichever asset they need or want inspired by those patterns and trends. It\'s a much richer brief than hey, uh we need a listicle with why'

[14:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we\'re better than 10 other CRM platforms and please always use the word accessible. And that can It helps you understand share model as a recommendation set. It helps you understand the perception of your brand'

[15:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
